Pirates hijacked the Saudi-owned super tanker Sirius Star off the African coast, taking it towards a Somali port.
The US Navy expressed concern over the pirates' ability to adapt tactics.
The fully-laden tanker was seized by armed men 420 nautical miles off Somalia.
NATO is considering long-term missions to counter piracy.
The hijacking highlighted the vulnerability of large ships in the Indian Ocean.
Somali pirates have become better armed and targeted bigger vessels.
The Saudi tanker, carrying $100 million worth of crude, was anchored off Somalia.
This incident marked a significant shift in pirate capabilities and tactics.
